### Handles (node-level pins)

|               |                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **When**      | Which handle an edge uses, handle Y position, crowding on one side                                                                                                                              |
| **Read**      | `schema-handles.ts`, `SchemaNode.tsx`                                                                                                                                                           |
| **Key idea**  | One handle per relationship end (`relationshipId` + source/target). **Not** tied to property rows. Y from `computePartnerAlignedHandleTops()` â€” partner node vertical center + collision spread |
| **Constants** | `MIN_HANDLE_GAP` 56, `SIDE_INSET` 18                                                                                                                                                            |
| **Don't**     | Let libavoid choose handles; don't sort handles by `relationshipId` for Y                                                                                                                       |

### Edge routing (libavoid)

|               |                                                                                                                                                                    |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **When**      | Orthogonal paths, edges through nodes, WASM load                                                                                                                   |
| **Read**      | `useLibavoid.ts`, `public/libavoid.wasm`                                                                                                                           |
| **Key idea**  | Shapes = measured node bounds; pins = React Flow `handleBounds`. Routes between fixed handles. `getHandleLayoutSignature` invalidates shapes when handle Y changes |
| **Constants** | `shapeBufferDistance` 28, `idealNudgingDistance` 24                                                                                                                |
| **Requires**  | `ReactFlowProvider`, `nodesInitialized`, measured node dimensions                                                                                                  |

### Transit clearance (obstacle nodes)

|               |                                                                                                                                                                  |
| ------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **When**      | Unrelated edge clips a node (e.g. Personâ†’Interaction over Organization)                                                                                          |
| **Read**      | `graph-clearance.ts`, GRAPH-ROUTING.md Â§ Transit clearance                                                                                                       |
| **Key idea**  | Edge path can be correct while a **middle-column node** needs to move. Two passes: post-dagre estimate, post-libavoid horizontal-segment scan (max 4 iterations) |
| **Constants** | `TRANSIT_NODE_CLEARANCE` 52 + `LABEL_CLEARANCE` 16                                                                                                               |
| **Don't**     | Reroute the edge â€” nudge obstructing nodes with `dy`                                                                                                             |

